For checking which PK files for <font> are used in <file> with given <mode>:

1. run 'tex? <file>' (change `?' to `+' if <mode> is `screen', to `-'
   if <mode> is `localfont')
2. generate all PK files shown in DVIFONT error(s) using <mode> and copy them to
   ~/tex/TeXfonts/<mode>/, if any (ignore DVIFONT error(s) for <font>, if any)
3. rm -f ~/tex/TeXfonts/<mode>/<font>.*
4. run 'tex? <file>' - the necessary PK files will be shown in DVIFONT error(s)
